TITLE: Question: How are some bars boosting profits? Answer: Trivia nights
SUMMARY: Across the country, many bars and restaurants have added trivia to bring in more guests and turn higher profits.

TITLE: Blocked emergency exits and 'dangerous' fire hazards: Dollar General again found in violation of federal workplace safety standards
SUMMARY: Discount retailer Dollar General, which has been fined $15 million for safety violations since 2017, was penalized for fire hazards at a Pennsylvania store.

TITLE: Airlines' answer for congested airports and rising costs: Bigger planes
SUMMARY: Airlines are turning to bigger planes that fit more travelers to handle strong demand.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond proposes reverse stock split as it struggles to avoid bankruptcy
SUMMARY: Bed Bath & Beyond wants to raise $300 million in a stock offering but needs shareholders to approve a reverse stock split at a May 9 meeting to make it happen.

TITLE: Walmart will add thousands of EV charging stations to stores by 2030
SUMMARY: The big-box retailer said it's in the process of identifying suppliers, though it plans to own and operate the EV charging stations in its national network.

TITLE: Michael Jordan sneakers, Kobe Bryant gear lead blockbuster Sotheby's auction
SUMMARY: Michael Jordan's signed 1998 sneakers are the cornerstone of a two-part Sotheby's auction of game-worn sports memorabilia.

TITLE: Disney names first brand chief as Iger refocuses on core properties
SUMMARY: Disney named Asad Ayaz as its first-ever chief brand officer, as CEO Bob Iger works to refocus the company on its core entertainment properties.

TITLE: Judge says he can compel Fox's Rupert and Lachlan Murdoch to testify live in Dominion trial
SUMMARY: Dominion Voting Systems is urging a Delaware judge to compel Fox execs Rupert Murdoch and Lachlan Murdoch to testify live in court.

TITLE: Ram's electric pickup will top the F-150 Lightning and GMC Hummer in EV range
SUMMARY: Stellantis executives said that while the 2025 Ram 1500 REV won't be first to market, it will offer leading capabilities.

TITLE: 'The Super Mario Bros. Movie' is set for a big opening weekend — despite bad reviews
SUMMARY: "The Super Mario Bros. Movie" has been poorly reviewed by critics, but box office analysts foresee a big opening weekend for the Nintendo video game adaptation.

TITLE: American Airlines scraps traditional frequent flyer award chart in dynamic pricing shift
SUMMARY: Starting Wednesday, American will publish starting levels for how many frequent flyer miles are likely required to redeem for a ticket in certain regions.

TITLE: Jeep unveils 2024 Wrangler SUV in next stage of off-road sales battle with Ford Bronco
SUMMARY: The 2024 Jeep Wrangler features an evolutionary exterior design and a redesigned interior that includes additional safety, convenience and tech options.

TITLE: Sweetgreen stock falls after Chipotle sues for trademark infringement over burrito bowl
SUMMARY: Sweetgreen launched its "Chipotle Chicken Burrito Bowl" less than a week ago.

TITLE: More movies, more variety, more money: The box office is catching up to pre-Covid levels
SUMMARY: A steady stream of mid-budgeted films from various genres has bolstered ticket sales, augmenting big business from blockbusters.

TITLE: Blockbuster pushed HBO to start investing in original content, cable giant's ex-chief says
SUMMARY: Blockbuster's emergence in the late 1980s fueled HBO to bet on original content, according to former HBO and Time Warner CEO Jeff Bewkes.

TITLE: Kia's new EV9 is a 7-passenger electric SUV coming to the U.S. late this year
SUMMARY: The automaker is aiming to sell 1.6 million EVs per year by 2030, CEO Ho Sung Song said during an investor presentation on Wednesday.

TITLE: Johnson & Johnson shares rise after company proposes baby powder cancer settlement
SUMMARY: Wall Street analysts were encouraged by J&J's proposal to pay $8.9 billion to settle claims that its baby powder and other talc products caused cancer.

TITLE: Lack of home listings is taking a toll on mortgage demand
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates fell last week, but lack of housing supply is keeping buyers at bay.

TITLE: Frank founder criminally charged with fraud over $175 million JPMorgan deal
SUMMARY: Prosecutors accused Charlie Javice of inflating Frank's user base before selling the startup to JPMorgan Chase.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond gets $120 million merchandise lifeline as it faces bankruptcy threat
SUMMARY: Hilco Global's ReStore Capital has agreed to buy up to $120 million in merchandise for Bed Bath & Beyond so it can boost its inventory levels.

TITLE: Virgin Orbit COO calls out company leadership for failures in goodbye memo. Read the full email
SUMMARY: An email from Virgin Orbit's outgoing Chief Operating Officer Tony Gingiss appears to call out CEO Dan Hart, although not by name.

TITLE: Johnson & Johnson to pay $8.9 billion to settle talc cancer claims
SUMMARY: Johnson & Johnson said it would pay an $8.9 billion settlement over claims that its talc-based baby powder caused cancer.

TITLE: GM overtakes Ford as second-best seller of EVs in U.S. but still trails Tesla by a wide margin
SUMMARY: General Motors pulled ahead of Ford Motor to become the country's second-best seller of electric vehicles during the first quarter.

TITLE: Cuba's losses in case of Castro-era debt open it up to more lawsuits
SUMMARY: Cuba will likely face more suits over billions of dollars' worth of unpaid commercial debts from the 1980s after a decision by a UK High Court judge.

TITLE: Goldman Sachs invests $2 billion in Black women-owned businesses — the first chapter of a bigger plan
SUMMARY: One Million Black Women launched in March 2021 with the bigger goal of having a positive impact on the lives of 1 million Black women by 2030.

TITLE: As retail gets choppy, Walmart flexes its grocery muscle, deep pockets and huge reach
SUMMARY: Walmart will hold an investor event this week in Tampa, Florida.

TITLE: GM says 5,000 salaried workers will take buyouts, expects $1 billion charge in first quarter
SUMMARY: About 5,000 white-collar workers at GM opted to participate in a buyout program to lower the automaker's global head count and fixed costs.

TITLE: Virgin Orbit files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection in the U.S.
SUMMARY: Virgin Orbit filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection after failing to secure a funding lifeline.

TITLE: Ford's first-quarter sales increase 10.1% on improved F-Series truck production
SUMMARY: Ford sold 475,906 vehicles during the first three months of the year, up 10.1% compared with subdued levels a year earlier due to supply chain problems.

TITLE: Women's soccer expands into the Bay Area with a new team and record investment
SUMMARY: The National Women's Soccer League has awarded a 14th franchise to an investor group in California's Bay Area for a record $53 million fee.
